<h2>15th Anniversary Gala - A Great Success!!</h2>
</div>
<p></p>
<p>06.15.13</p>
<div class="newsbody"><p>A capacity crowd filled Ada Slaiter Hall at Daniel's Spectrum in Regent Park on Wednesday June 12th as over 250 former residents, volunteers, friends and supporters gathered to celebrate our 15th anniversary of welcoming refugee claimants from around the world.&nbsp; An&nbsp;interactive reception and silent auction followed by music by Krystaal, an international buffet, special videos and captivating speakers made it a very memorable event.&nbsp;&nbsp;The evening ended with everyone singing &quot;Happy Birthday&quot; to Matthew House followed by the consumption of delicious cupcakes by Yummy Stuff bakery.&nbsp; And the best news of all, we reached our goal of raising $50,000!!<strong>&nbsp; </strong>Thank you to all who attended.</p>
<p><img alt="" width="683" height="1024" src="/site/ywd_trialsite_1564/assets/images/Anne_comp_d_at_gala_backdrop_June__13.jpg" /></p>
<p>Founder and Executive Director Anne Woolger above, addressing crowd at 15th Anniversary Gala.</p></div>
